getOwnProperty

public Vector<String> getOwnProperty(String property)
Return only the objects with the following form: inputProperty retValue inputProperty is the parameter as string and retValue will be returned. If there are more than one match all results are returned.

Parameters:
property - The property as String that should be read out.
Returns:
All objects that matches the query.

getAllProperty

public Vector<String> getAllProperty(String property)
Return all object of the form: [] inputProperty retValue inputProperty is the parameter as string and retValue will be returned. The subject doesn't matter. If there are more than one match all results are returned.

Parameters:
property - The property as String that should be read out.
Returns:
All objects that matches the query.
